# Local install targets for `./gradlew installJars` (see docs/TESTING.md).
#
# Copy this file to `mods-install.env` (gitignored) and set each line to the
# `mods` folder of the matching Minecraft instance. `installJars` runs
# `chiseledBuild` and then copies each variant's jar into the folder set here.
#
# - Key = Stonecutter variant name (`<mcVersion>-<loader>`), exactly as below.
# - Value = absolute path to that instance's `mods` folder (raw, unescaped —
#   Windows backslashes are fine; surrounding quotes are optional).
# - Leave a line blank / commented to skip that variant.
# - Before copying, any existing `minegasm-*.jar` in the target folder is
#   removed first, so a version bump never leaves two Minegasm jars behind.

26.2-neoforge=
26.2-fabric=
26.2-forge=

26.1.2-neoforge=
26.1.2-fabric=
26.1.2-forge=

# Example (delete the leading '# ' and adjust):
# 26.2-neoforge=C:\Users\me\AppData\Roaming\.minecraft-neoforge-26.2\mods
# 26.2-fabric=C:\Users\me\curseforge\minecraft\Instances\Fabric 26.2\mods
